<blockquote>
<p><strong>Most advice about local photos is wrong.</strong> People are told to upload "as many as possible." That is backwards. Twelve well-tagged, cross-platform-consistent photos beat 80 random uploads in visual search rankings. Volume creates noise. Consistency creates ranking.</p>
